	<h1>Root Servers</h1>

	<p>The authoritative name servers that serve the DNS root zone, commonly known as the “root servers”, are a network
		of hundreds of servers in many countries around the world. They are configured in the DNS root zone as 13 named
		authorities, as follows.</p>

	<h2>List of Root Servers</h2>
	
